    "recap_headline": "University of Northern Colorado Athletics",
    "recap_text": "OMAHA, Neb.\n\u2013 Northern Colorado outlasted Omaha in a back-and-forth battle on Sunday afternoon, using a clutch extra-inning push to secure an 8-7 victory at Tal Anderson Field and claim the weekend series.\nNorthern Colorado struck first in the opening frame, as\nLogan Pruski\ndelivered an RBI single to plate\nJake Bullard\nand give the Bears an early 1-0 lead. Omaha quickly answered in the bottom half, tying the game at 1-1, setting the tone for a tightly contested afternoon.\nAfter trading scoreless innings, UNC regained control in the fourth when\nSam Pease\ncame through with an RBI single, followed by a two-run fifth inning highlighted by Pruski's RBI double and a run-scoring groundout from\nMason Griffin\nto extend the lead to 4-2. The Bears continued to apply pressure in the sixth, capitalizing on patience at the plate.\nJaden Stone\nand Bullard each drew bases-loaded walks to push the advantage to 6-2. UNC added another insurance run in the seventh behind Pease's third hit of the day, an RBI single that made it 7-3 and put the Bears in a strong position late.\nOmaha refused to go quietly. A dramatic four-run rally in the bottom of the ninth tied the game at 7-7, forcing extra innings. UNC\u00a0quickly responded in the 10th, after Stone led off with a single and advanced into scoring position. Griffin delivered the go-ahead RBI single to score Stone and give the Bears an 8-7 edge.\nOn the mound, the Bears pieced together the final outs to secure the win.\nBrady Hudson\nearned the victory after recording a key out in the ninth, while\nLogan Borboa\nshut the door in the 10th to pick up the save.\nAt the plate, Pease led the way with a standout performance, going 3-for-4 with two RBIs and two stolen bases. Pruski added two hits and two RBIs, while Stone reached base three times and scored twice.\nNorthern Colorado totaled 13 hits and worked six walks, consistently putting pressure on Omaha's pitching staff throughout the game. With the win, the Bears secure the series and carry momentum into their next stretch of conference play.\nON DECK:\nNorthern Colorado returns to Greeley for a three-game conference series against South Dakota State, beginning Friday, March 27. First pitch is set for 2 p.m. MDT.\nDIAMOND CLUB\nThe Diamond Club plays a vital role in supporting the UNC Baseball program. By giving to the Diamond Club, you help provide access to facility enhancements\u2014such as the Jackson Field Turf Project\u2014along with advanced technology and elevated daily operations, giving our student-athletes the resources to compete and excel at the highest level.\nGive to the Diamond Club today!\nFOLLOW THE BEARS\nFor complete coverage of UNC Athletics, visit uncbears.com. Follow the baseball team on X (formerly Twitter) (@UNC_BearsBSB) and Instagram (@UNC_BearsBaseball).",
